gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Celtics 136, Nets 86
gameRecap.excerpt: The Celtics win their sixth straight game as they defeat the Nets, 136-86. Payton Pritchard led the way for the Celtics with a game-high 28 points (6-9 3PT FG), while Derrick White (27 points, 5-10 3PT FG) and Jayson Tatum (20 points, seven rebounds, nine assists) added a combined 47 points in the victory. Mikal Bridges notched 10 points, four rebounds and four assists for the Nets in the losing effort. The Celtics have won eight out of their last ten games as they improve to 43-12 on the season, while the Nets fall to 21-33.
